<TITLE> Sahara leads probe team into BDR HQ </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Feb 28 (bdnews24.com)Home minister Sahara Khatun led members of a probe committee into BDR headquarters on Saturday, two days after the mutiny by armed border guards was quelled. She asked Dhaka police commissioner Naeem Ahmed to ensure no evidence was disturbed ahead of the investigation. "All of the evidence must be properly preserved," she said, pointing to the bullet-ridden car of slain BDR chief Maj Gen Shakil Ahmed that had been left uncovered. The government named the ten-member committee on Friday, headed by the home minister, to investigate the mutiny within Bangladesh Rifles ranks, which left scores of officers dead. At least 77 bodies, mostly slain army officers including BDR chief Major General Shakil Ahmed, had been unearthed within the BDR compound in Dhaka up to Saturday noon . bd
